[1] USA (Minnesota)
Date: Mon 21 Mar 2011
Source: StarTribune.com [abbreviated & edited]
<http://www.startribune.com/lifestyle/health/118403109.html>


The Minnesota Department of Health reported Monday [21 Mar 2011] that
a 7-month-old had the measles, bringing the total in this outbreak to
7. Three cases involve Somali children who are old enough to receive
the measles vaccine but haven't. Another 3 involve infants who are too
young to receive the vaccine.

The outbreak probably started with an infant who returned from Kenya
last month [February 2011], the Health Department said. Health
officials are hoping more parents in the Somali community will seek
shots after a forum Saturday [19 Mar 2011] to address their concerns
about vaccine safety.

[Byline: Jeremy Olson]

--
